history.content: Opportunity Through Data is hosting our very own Assistant Vice Chancellor for Student Equity and Success, Fabrizio Mejia - tonight @ 7pm PST! The programs under his oversight include the Basic Needs Center, the Centers for Educational Equity and Excellence (CE3), the Disabled Students Program, and Equity and Inclusion STEM Programs. We'll be taking audience questions the entire duration of the event so its a great opportunity to learn and ask questions about campus goals on student equity, and managing the effects of the pandemic on the student body. RSVP here: https://www.facebook.com/events/196574408684013
history.subject: Fireside Chat with Assistant Vice Chancellor for Student Equity and Success!
